/Month><Day>18</Day></PubMedPubDate></History><PublicationStatus>epublish</PublicationStatus><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">40385899</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC12085864</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"doi\">10.7759/cureus.82509</ArticleId></ArticleIdList><ReferenceList><Reference><Citation>Addressing the role of edaravone in the management of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis and gaps in care and access: expert panel recommendations. Barrington CJ, Burruano M, Carney C, et al.  https://doi.org/10.37765/ajmc.2021.88732 Am J Manag Care. 2021;27:0&#x2013;7.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">34382759</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Effects of the edaravone, a drug approved for the treatment of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis, on mitochondrial function and neuroprotection. Cha SJ, Kim K. http://dx.doi.org/10.3390/antiox11020195. Antioxidants (Basel) 2022;11:195.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC8868074</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">35204078</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Multiple system atrophy. Fanciulli A, Stankovic I, Krismer F, Seppi K, Levin J, Wenning GK. https://doi.org/10.1016/bs.irn.2019.10.004. Int Rev Neurobiol. 2019;149:137&#x2013;192.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">31779811</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Atypical parkinsonism of Japan: amyotrophic lateral sclerosis-parkinsonism-dementia complex of the Kii peninsula of Japan (Muro disease): an update. Kuzuhara S, Kokubo Y. https://doi.org/10.1002/mds.20548 Mov Disord. 2005;20:0&#x2013;13.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">16092099</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Improving diagnostic accuracy of multiple system atrophy: a clinicopathological study. Miki Y, Foti SC, Asi YT, Tsushima E, Quinn N, Ling H, Holton JL. https://doi.org/10.1093/brain/awz189. Brain. 2019;142:2813&#x2013;2827.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">31289815</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Mitsui J, Tsuji S. Trials for Cerebellar Ataxias. Contemporary Clinical Neuroscience. Cham, Switzerland: Springer; 2023. Coenzyme Q10 in multiple system atrophy; pp. 679&#x2013;690.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>Investigating edaravone use for management of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS): a narrative review. Neupane P, Thada PK, Singh P, et al.  https://doi.org/10.7759/cureus.33746 Cureus. 2023;15:0.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC9922523</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">36788871</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Neuregulins in neurodegenerative diseases. Ou GY, Lin WW, Zhao WJ. https://doi.org/10.3389/fnagi.2021.662474. Front Aging Neurosci. 2021;13:662474.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC8064692</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">33897409</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>The hot cross bun sign: a journey across etiologies. Prasad S, Rossi M. https://doi.org/10.1002/mdc3.13596. Mov Disord Clin Pract. 2022;9:1018&#x2013;1020.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC9631848</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">36339309</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>The dual nature of Onuf's nucleus: neuroanatomical features and peculiarities, in health and disease. Schellino R, Boido M, Vercelli A. https://doi.org/10.3389/fnana.2020.572013. Front Neuroanat. 2020;14:1&#x2013;13.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC7500142</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">33013330</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>ERBB4 mutations that disrupt the neuregulin-ErbB4 pathway cause amyotrophic lateral sclerosis type 19. Takahashi Y, Fukuda Y, Yoshimura J, et al.  https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ajhg.2013.09.008. Am J Hum Genet. 2013;93:900&#x2013;905.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC3824132</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">24119685</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Analysis of ErbB4 variants in amyotrophic lateral sclerosis within a Chinese cohort. Wang F, Liu X, He J, Zhang N, Chen L, Tang L, Fan D. https://doi.org/10.3389/fneur.2022.865264. Front Neurol. 2022;13:865264.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC9035935</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">35481267</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Multiple system atrophy: advances in diagnosis and therapy. Watanabe H, Shima S, Mizutani Y, Ueda A, Ito M. https://doi.org/10.14802/jmd.22082. J Mov Disord. 2023;16:13&#x2013;21.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType=\"pmc\">PMC9978260</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType=\"pubmed\">36537066</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference></ReferenceList></PubmedData></PubmedArticle><PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status=\"MEDLINE\" Owner=\"NLM\" IndexingMethod=\"Automated\"><PMID Version=\"1\">40409555</PMID><DateCompleted><Year>2025</Year><Month>08</Month><Day>02</Day></DateCompleted><DateRevised><Year>2026</Year><Month>02</Month><Day>24</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel=\"Print-Electronic\"><Journal><ISSN IssnType=\"Electronic\">1083-351X</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium=\"Internet\"><Volume>301</Volume><Issue>7</Issue><PubDate><Year>2025</Year><Month>Jul</Month></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>The Journal of biological chemistry</Title><ISOAbbreviation>J Biol Chem</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>Abnormal regulation of membrane-less organelles contributes to profilin1-associated ALS.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>110259</StartPage><MedlinePgn>110259</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType=\"pii\" ValidYN=\"Y\">110259</ELocationID><ELocationID EIdType=\"doi\" ValidYN=\"Y\">10.1016/j.jbc.2025.110259</ELocationID><ELocationID EIdType=\"pii\" ValidYN=\"Y\">S0021-9258(25)02109-X</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>Profilin 1 (PFN1) is a key cytoskeletal protein that regulates actin dynamics by incorporating monomeric actin into linear filaments. PFN1 deletion or mutations have been linked to numerous neurodegenerative diseases, including amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS). However, the contribution of PFN1 to neurodegenerative pathologies is poorly understood. Recent studies have implicated the role of aberrant cellular membrane-less organelles (MLOs) in neurodegenerative pathogenesis. Here, we demonstrate that PFN1 is involved in the assembly of MLOs, including Cajal bodies and Stress granules. Specifically, depletion of PFN1 leads to abnormal Cajal body accumulation and accelerated maturation into a gel-like state, consequently dysregulating snRNP biogenesis and impairing pre-mRNA splicing efficiency in both neuronal and non-neuronal cells. Similarly, we show that PFN1 knockdown accelerates the assembly of Stress granules in stressed cells. Furthermore, we demonstrate that the ALS-linked PFN1-C71 G mutant exhibits a loss of function in the context of MLO biogenesis. We further reveal that the PFN1 deficiency-induced Cajal body dysregulation, but not Stress granule assembly, is caused by cellular actin filament depolymerization. Importantly, the actin filament agonist CN04 rescues Cajal body properties in PFN1-depleted cells. Taken together, our findings shed light on the role of PFN1 in MLO biogenesis and suggest its involvement in neurodegenerative pathogenesis.</AbstractText><CopyrightInformation>Copyright &#xa9; 2025 The Authors. Published by Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.</CopyrightInformation></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN=\"Y\"><Author ValidYN=\"Y\"><LastName>Ma</LastName><ForeName>Guoqiang</ForeName><Initials>G</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Jiangsu Key Laboratory of Drug Discovery and Translational Research for Brain Diseases, College of Pharmaceutical Sciences, Soochow University, Suzhou, Jiangsu, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN=\"Y\"><La